nsional HM $pp$ data analysis. For PYTHIA Monash\ngenerated sets of data, the strength of the intermittency is found to vary\nsignificantly with the variation of the strength of the color reconnection (CR)\nparameter, i.e., reconnection range RR, for RR = 0.0, 1.8 and 3.0, thereby,\nestablishing a strong connection between the CR mechanism and the observed\nintermittent type of emission of primary charged particles of the studied\nhigh-multiplicity $pp$ events.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 25 Feb 2019 07:51:26 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-03-06"}
