 errors of $0.42\\%$ and $0.065\\%$ for the\n$\\bar{C}_{20}$ and $\\bar{C}_{22}$ spherical harmonic gravity field\ncoefficients, respectively. These values are below current uncertainties, but\norders of magnitude larger than those obtained from past simulations for\naccurate tracking of a future Phobos lander.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 25 Feb 2019 11:07:31 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-02-26"}
